==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wich
<hw>Wich</hw>
<pr>(w⟦icr⟧ch)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧c</ets>
village, fr. L. <ets>vicus</ets>. In some names of places, perhaps fr.
Icel. <ets>v⟦imac⟧k</ets> an inlet, creek, bay. See <er>Vicinity</er>,
and cf. <er>Villa</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A street; a village; a castle; a dwelling; a place
of work, or exercise of authority; -- now obsolete except in
composition; <as>as, baili<ex>wick</ex>, War<ex>wick</ex>,
Green<ex>wick</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Stow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Curling)</fld> <def>A narrow port or passage in the
rink or course, flanked by the stones of previous players.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>wick</ent>⟦br⟧
